let (s0: (Set[Set[ℝ]], Set[ℝ], Set[ℝ]) -> Set[ℝ], s1: Set[Set[ℝ]] -> Set[ℝ], s2: Set[Set[ℝ]] -> Set[ℝ]) satisfy { forall(x0: Set[Set[ℝ]], x1: Set[ℝ], x2: Set[ℝ]) { not subset_two_intersection[ℝ](x0) or not x1 ∈ x0 or not x2 ∈ x0 or s0(x0, x1, x2) ∈ x0 } and forall(x3: Set[Set[ℝ]], x4: Set[ℝ], x5: Set[ℝ]) { not subset_two_intersection[ℝ](x3) or not x4 ∈ x3 or not x5 ∈ x3 or s0(x3, x4, x5) ⊆ x4 ∩ x5 } and forall(x6: Set[Set[ℝ]]) { s1(x6) ∈ x6 or subset_two_intersection[ℝ](x6) } and forall(x7: Set[Set[ℝ]]) { s2(x7) ∈ x7 or subset_two_intersection[ℝ](x7) } and forall(x8: Set[ℝ], x9: Set[Set[ℝ]]) { not x8 ⊆ s1(x9) ∩ s2(x9) or not x8 ∈ x9 or subset_two_intersection[ℝ](x9) } }
not empty[Set[ℝ]].is_empty or not s1(empty[Set[ℝ]]) ∈ empty[Set[ℝ]]
not no_empty[ℝ](Set[ℝ].empty_set) or not subset_two_intersection[ℝ](Set[ℝ].empty_set) or is_set_net[ℝ](Set[ℝ].empty_set)
not all_closed_interval(Set[ℝ].empty_set) or not is_set_net[ℝ](Set[ℝ].empty_set) or is_closed_interval_net(Set[ℝ].empty_set)
